  "canonical_term": "Keltner Channels",
  "aliases": [
    "kelner channels",
    "Kelner channels"
  ],
  "school": "Indicator-Based",
  "definition": "A volatility-based envelope indicator with a middle exponential moving average (default 20) and bands derived from adding/subtracting a multiple of the Average True Range (ATR). The ATR smoothing produces bands that are less spiky than Bollinger Bands.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "The indicator consists of three lines: a middle EMA (typically 20-period), an upper band at EMA + (Multiplier × ATR), and a lower band at EMA - (Multiplier × ATR).",
    "Default settings use Length 20, Multiplier 2, exponential MA, and ATR calculation.",
    "The bands appear smoother and less prone to sharp spikes compared to Bollinger Bands."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Not explicitly stated in the material.",
  "common_mistakes": [
